installations :

npx ts-jest config:init

Then for jest to read typescript files, ts-node needs to be installed and available in your package.json file.

Use npm install -g ts-node and npm install --save-dev ts.node

// YOUTUBE TUTORIAL STARTS HERE :

- Go to Nexjs testing docs (Straight to Jest and React Testing Library configuration page) through : https://nextjs.org/docs/pages/building-your-application/optimizing/testing#jest-and-react-testing-library
- Create files (jest.config.js) and (jest.setup.js) in your main folder diretory
- from the Next docs, copy and paste the content of the jest.config.js and jest.setup.js files, into your own jest.config.js and jest.setup.js files respectively.
- Paste (import '@testing-library/jest-dom') inside the jest.setup.js file
- Go to your package.json file and add ("test": "jest",
  "coverage" : "jest --coverage") in the scripts config object
